  "title": "Process Engineer (Process Industry I Chemical Plant I West)",
  "description": "<ul><li><strong>Well Established Company</strong></li><li><strong>Basic $4000 - $4500 + AWS + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li><strong>Excellent Welfare and Benefits + Career progression</strong></li><li><strong>Working location : Tuas (Transport Provided)</strong></li><li><strong>Working days : Monday to Friday</strong></li><li><strong>Working hours : 8am to 5pm</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Analyze and evaluate existing processes, take measurements and interpret data including SCADA system operations (in line with company towards digitalization)</strong></li><li>Perform risk assessments</li><li><strong>Research, design, and develop processes to optimize productivity and workflow</strong></li><li><strong>Oversee operations and maintenance of facility processes</strong></li><li>Determine the organization and setup of operations</li><li><strong>Oversee implementation of new processes and procedures</strong></li><li><strong>Investigate and troubleshoot any problems that arise with processes, procedures, and operations</strong></li><li><strong>Develop best practices, routines and innovative solutions to improve throughput and quality of output</strong></li><li>Manage cost and time constraints</li><li>Provide process documentation and operating instructions</li><li><strong>Involve and perform PSM and Hazop study</strong></li><li><strong>Become turn key manager to plan and execute plant shutdown</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Chemical Engineering with at least 1 year of process industry experience</li><li><strong>Strong working knowledge of process related standards, Process Improvement and Safety Management</strong></li><li>Team oriented and dynamic</li></ul><p>Candidates are encouraged to apply this position via <strong>Apply Now</strong> button with the following information in the resume</p><ul><li>Work experiences and job responsibilities</li><li>Current and Expected salary</li><li>Reason for leaving</li><li>Date of availability</li><li>Education background</li></ul><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</p><p><br /></p><p>THIEN CHING MEI (R2198032)<br />EA Recruitment Pte Ltd<br />EA License No: 21C0492</p>",
